headline: Oil prices expected to fall in 2026 as Wall Street sees 'punishing oversupply' risking return to COVID levels
summary: Wall Street's biggest banks see oil prices falling into the $50s or lower per barrel in 2026 and beyond, teeing up a tough year for the oil and gas industry.
